------------------- Project Setup ----------------------
1. create a folder fun-chat
    then initilize the git inside it
2. create 2 folders(backend , frontend) inside fun-chat
3. go inside frontend and create a vite@latest project
4. come to fun-chat and type npm "npm init"
5. create server.js inside backend folder 

6. come to backend folder do the following _________

install some packages in backend project like :- 
express,dotenv,cookie-parser , bcryptjs , 
mongoose , socket.it , jsonwebtoken

express :- to initialize a web server
dotenv :- to store environment variables
cookie-parser :- to parse the cookies
bcryptjs :- to convert the passowrds into hashpasswords
mongoose :- to connect with mongodb server
socket.io :- to create realtime communication 
jsonwebtoken :- to create socket.io tokens

* and install nodemon as dev dependency *

7. Now test your express with a simple "/" route

